&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Every developer has a tab open on Stack Overflow.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;We are one of the most popular websites in the world - a community-based space focused on increasing productivity, decreasing cycle times, accelerating time to market, and protecting institutional knowledge.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Innovation is at the heart of everything we do. We embrace collaboration, transparency, and believe in leading with empathy; creating an environment where every Stacker knows they belong. We embrace that the unique contributions and points of view of all Stackers contribute to our success.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We are a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Best Company to Work For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;, in addition to being recognized for Best Company Leadership, Best Company Happiness, Best Company Perks and Benefits, Best Company Work-Life Balance, Best Company Compensation, and Best Company Outlook.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;We are a remote-first company with Hiring HUBs based in the US, Canada, UK, and Germany.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Stack Overflow is in the middle of one of the most consequential pivots of its history. We are transforming from the world’s largest developer community to a unified knowledge platform for both humans and agents with our enterprise product as the centerpiece, shaping how organizations will govern and retrieve trusted knowledge at scale. Stack Overflow has assets that no one else has—years of trust signals, developer credibility, and community generated knowledge that AI systems can actually rely on.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The design problems that come with this are genuinely hard. Without a traditional UI, the experience lives inside chat responses, API calls, and contexts we don’t fully own which means design here is heavily weighted toward information architecture, content strategy, and the quality of language. We’re shipping at a pace that requires designers to work closer to code than ever before and that expectation will only grow.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Director of Product Design and Research owns how the product looks, feels, works, and how we know if it’s working for users. You’ll report to the CPTO, shape strategy at the leadership level, and stay close enough to the work to raise its quality and support and advocate on behalf of the people doing it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team is experienced, capable, and already oriented in this direction. They don’t need rebuilding. They need a leader who will help them work with confidence, maintain craft standards under speed and pressure while adopting new ways of working and advocating for the team when it matters.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
